description: Best practices for Laravel applications in a TALL stack context

Use Eloquent Relationships for efficient and readable data retrieval.
Implement Middleware for route protection, access control, and request manipulation.
Utilize Service Providers and a Service Layer for better organization of complex business logic.
Follow PSR standards for consistent and clean code.
Use Form Requests for validation to keep controllers lean and validation logic organized.
Queue Jobs for long-running tasks to prevent blocking HTTP requests and improve user experience.
Write Feature and Unit Tests to ensure code reliability and prevent regressions.

